{"title":"The Obligation to Be Happy","author":{"name":"Linda Pastan"},"publishDate":"2011-10-18","lines":[{"line":"It is more onerous","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"than the rites of beauty","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"or housework, harder than love.","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"But you expect it of me casually,","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"the way you expect the sun","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"to come up, not in spite of rain","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"or clouds but because of them.","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"And so I smile, as if my own fidelity","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"to sadness were a hidden vice—","stanza":2,"number":9},{"line":"that downward tug on my mouth,","stanza":2,"number":10},{"line":"my old suspicion that health","stanza":2,"number":11},{"line":"and love are brief irrelevancies,","stanza":2,"number":12},{"line":"no more than laughter in the warm dark","stanza":2,"number":13},{"line":"strangled at dawn.","stanza":2,"number":14},{"line":"Happiness. I try to hoist it","stanza":3,"number":15},{"line":"on my narrow shoulders again—","stanza":3,"number":16},{"line":"a knapsack heavy with gold coins.","stanza":3,"number":17},{"line":"I stumble around the house,","stanza":3,"number":18},{"line":"bump into things.","stanza":3,"number":19},{"line":"Only Midas himself","stanza":3,"number":20},{"line":"would understand.","stanza":3,"number":21}]}